<caption box="[151,1428,1987,2011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" startId="18.[151,255,1987,2011]" targetBox="[158,1429,938,1961]" targetPageId="18">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1428,1987,2011]" box="[151,1428,1987,2011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,327,1987,2011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">FIGURE 10. A,</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hickson" authorityYear="1928" box="[334,588,1988,2011]" class="Anthozoa" family="Gorgoniidae" genus="Leptogorgia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Alcyonacea" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="californica">
<emphasis box="[334,588,1988,2011]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Leptogorgia californica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(YPM 1713, lectotype); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[855,873,1987,2011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">B</emphasis>
, detail of a branch; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1086,1105,1987,2011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">C</emphasis>
, light micrograph of sclerites.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,152,738]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,476,311,337]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<typeStatus box="[198,322,311,337]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Lectotype</typeStatus>
description.
</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[536,643,312,338]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a small, dry fragment 
<quantity box="[935,1015,312,338]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="cm" value="2.5">2.5 cm</quantity>
in length, and 
<quantity box="[1189,1268,312,338]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="cm" value="1.3">1.3 cm</quantity>
in width (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,255,1987,2011]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,938,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-221@18.[158,1429,934,1961]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. A, Leptogorgia californica (YPM 1713, lectotype); B, detail of a branch; C, light micrograph of sclerites." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 10A</figureCitation>
). According to Verrill (1868b) the form of the colonies is “somewhat flabelliform, subpinnately branched, branches ascending, not coalescent”. Branches are around 
<quantity box="[955,1022,392,418]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in diameter. Polyps are arranged in about three rows around the branches, they retract into nearly flat protuberances in the coenenchyme leaving slit-like apertures (
<figureCitation box="[376,523,472,498]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,255,1987,2011]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,938,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-221@18.[158,1429,934,1961]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. A, Leptogorgia californica (YPM 1713, lectotype); B, detail of a branch; C, light micrograph of sclerites." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 10A, B</figureCitation>
). Colour is reddish purple, and yellow longitudinal grooves appear in some parts along the branches. Sclerites of the coenenchyme are mostly red and pink, some are yellow, and some bicoloured; they are mostly capstans (
<figureCitation box="[597,704,552,578]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,255,1987,2011]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,938,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-221@18.[158,1429,934,1961]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. A, Leptogorgia californica (YPM 1713, lectotype); B, detail of a branch; C, light micrograph of sclerites." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
), which reach up to 
<quantity box="[945,1049,552,578]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.10 mm</quantity>
in length, and 
<quantity box="[1226,1331,552,578]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
in width (
<figureCitation box="[159,277,592,618]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,255,1987,2011]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,938,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-221@18.[158,1429,934,1961]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. A, Leptogorgia californica (YPM 1713, lectotype); B, detail of a branch; C, light micrograph of sclerites." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs. 10C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[290,321,592,618]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,255,2012,2036]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,781,2002]" captionTargetId="figure-275@19.[157,1431,771,2046]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Leptogorgia californica (YPM 1713, lectotype), SEM of coenenchymal sclerites, and anthocodial rods." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">11</figureCitation>
). Spindles occur in minor proportions; some of them with one end bent. The spindles reach up to 
<quantity box="[180,284,632,658]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.13">0.13 mm</quantity>
in length and 
<quantity box="[449,553,632,658]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.05">0.05 mm</quantity>
in width (
<figureCitation box="[672,777,632,658]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,255,1987,2011]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,938,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-221@18.[158,1429,934,1961]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. A, Leptogorgia californica (YPM 1713, lectotype); B, detail of a branch; C, light micrograph of sclerites." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 10C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[789,820,632,658]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,255,2012,2036]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,781,2002]" captionTargetId="figure-275@19.[157,1431,771,2046]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Leptogorgia californica (YPM 1713, lectotype), SEM of coenenchymal sclerites, and anthocodial rods." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">11</figureCitation>
). Crosses up to 0.08 by 
<quantity box="[1099,1202,632,658]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.07">0.07 mm</quantity>
occasionally occur; they have short rays with blunt warty ends (
<figureCitation box="[664,750,672,698]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,255,2012,2036]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,781,2002]" captionTargetId="figure-275@19.[157,1431,771,2046]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Leptogorgia californica (YPM 1713, lectotype), SEM of coenenchymal sclerites, and anthocodial rods." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). The anthocodial sclerites are slender, pale orange, somewhat flattened rods, up to 
<quantity box="[456,561,712,738]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.07">0.07 mm</quantity>
in length, and 
<quantity box="[736,839,712,738]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="0.02">0.02 mm</quantity>
in width, with lobed margins (
<figureCitation box="[1200,1318,712,738]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="18.[151,255,1987,2011]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,938,1961]" captionTargetId="figure-221@18.[158,1429,934,1961]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 10. A, Leptogorgia californica (YPM 1713, lectotype); B, detail of a branch; C, light micrograph of sclerites." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs. 10C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1330,1361,712,738]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="19.[151,255,2012,2036]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,781,2002]" captionTargetId="figure-275@19.[157,1431,771,2046]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 11. Leptogorgia californica (YPM 1713, lectotype), SEM of coenenchymal sclerites, and anthocodial rods." pageId="19" pageNumber="20">11</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
